-- Australia shares gain 1 pct as positive Fed talk sparks relief
-- By Byron Kaye
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 12:48AM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 18 (Reuters) - Australian shares rose 1 percent on Thursday as an upbeat economic assessment from the Federal Reserve triggered a relief-rally in global markets that had been unnerved by Russian financial turmoil and tumbling oil prices. [ID:nL3N0U2197]

The S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> added 0.95 percent or 48.94 points to 5210.80, its biggest one-day rally since Dec. 19, 2013, their biggest one-day gain since Dec. 2.